<p>In collaboration with the SFU Library and my fellow grad students, I’ve written a LaTeX template from which graduate students at Simon Fraser University can start writing their thesis or dissertation.</p>



<p><a href="https://github.com/rchurchley/sfuthesis/">The project</a>&nbsp;offers a LaTeX class file called&nbsp;<code>sfuthesis</code>&nbsp;that automatically sets your thesis according to the SFU Library’s style requirements. With its help, you can focus on writing up your research instead of fiddling with formatting.</p>



<p>Get started now by downloading a copy from the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.lib.sfu.ca/help/publish/thesis/templates#latex-template">SFU Library website</a>!</p>
